Patch Set 2:

Hi Hemanth,
Thank's for your review.

Type validation as well as range checking can be done using the 'args' decorator. For range checking we can pass 'type=validation_function' to the decorator.
But current parser design by passes args decorator for positional arguments. For e.g.

$ glance-manage db sync --version 47 --current_version 44 # validation will be done via args

$ glance-manage db sync 47 44 # args is bypassed in this case.

To add validation for 'version' and 'current_version' in case of both positional and optional arguments 
we need to make them as a positional arguments.
